## Drill down — `aaaaaaaa-acme-support.jsonl`

One JSON object per line: line 1 is the thread header, the rest are timeline entries keyed by `type`. Pull the FULL detail with jq:

```sh
jq -r 'select(.type=="delivery")' aaaaaaaa-acme-support.jsonl   # every outbound/callback delivery
jq -r 'select(.type=="log") | .label + " " + .detail' aaaaaaaa-acme-support.jsonl   # pipeline steps
jq -r 'select(.type=="draft" or .type=="note")' aaaaaaaa-acme-support.jsonl   # placed artifacts
jq -r 'select(.type=="thread").triage_result' aaaaaaaa-acme-support.jsonl   # the triage decision blob
```
